## Domain Relationship Rules

- A user represents identity and authentication only.
- A user may own one or multiple channels.
- A channel is the public content creation entity.
- Every video belongs exclusively to a channel, never directly to a user.
- Users subscribe to channels, not to users.
- A subscription represents the relationship between a user and a channel.
- Subscriptions may be free or paid.
- Channels define subscription plans with pricing and billing periods.
- Paid subscriptions reference a plan defined by the channel.
- Payments record financial transactions associated with paid subscriptions.
